	<section class="fluid-container newspage-news-items clearfix">
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-west-virginia">
						Understanding Medical Cannabis Laws in West Virginia
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/e92c4094040680166d5c7398299979e7e49e5492.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">West Virginia passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">2010 through Senate Bill 386</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. The law allows qualifying patients to possess a 30-day supply of medical marijuana, the amount is to be determined.</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-west-virginia" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-washington-dc">
						Facts on Medical Marijuana Legislation in Washington DC
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/0140cc03e49ed3614203aec15a0dc91cb6b3f862.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Washington DC (District of Columbia) passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2010 through an Amendment Act that was approved in a 13-0 vote. The law allows qualifying patients to possess&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">2-ounces of medical marijuana</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-washington-dc" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-washington">
						Positive Laws on Medical Marijuana in Washington
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/4271faa6a3f34e65214ff135cfae049c82cdd281.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Washington was the second state to legalize medical cannabis. Legalization was done through Initiative 692 that&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">was passed in 1998 with 59% of the vote</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. The law allows qualifying patients to possess 8-ounces of medical marijuana and cultivate up to 6 plants.</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-washington" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-vermont">
						Cannabis as Medicine in Vermont: Laws and Applying Procedures You Need to Know
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/31ccb98a0354d2cb1c8c01f6f17203c69f6ef169.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Vermont&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">legalized medical cannabis in 2004&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">through Senate Bill 76 and House Bill 645. The law allows qualifying patients to possess 2-ounces of medical marijuana and cultivate up to&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">9 plants&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">(2 mature, 7 immature).&nbsp;</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-vermont" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-rhode-island">
						Laws on Medical Cannabis in Rhode Island
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/6d6d683d53f1978b130b85a850780d29889e54bf.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Rhode Island passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">2006 through Senate Bill 0710</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. The law allows qualifying patients to possess 2.5 ounces of medical marijuana and cultivate&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">12 plants</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-rhode-island" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-pennsylvania">
						Facts on Pennsylvania Medical Marijuana Laws and Legal Procedures
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/f7131384ca7056f0c995551e0963a2def888fd8b.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(112, 87, 75);">Pennsylvania passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2016 through Senate Bill 3. The law allows qualifying patients to p</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">ossess a&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">30-day supply&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">of medical marijuana. Cultivation of medical marijuana is not allowed.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-pennsylvania" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-oregon">
						Medical Cannabis Laws in Oregon Explained
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/9245d894e7c025b4af67f866b82a1af7d7af4769.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Oregon passed a law to legalize medical marijuana in 1998 through a Ballot Measure that received&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">55% of the vote</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. The law allows qualifying patients to possess 24-ounces of medical marijuana and cultivate up to&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">24 plants&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">(6 mature, 18 immature).</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-oregon" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-ohio">
						Introduction to Ohio Medical Marijuana Laws
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/1f187b97f551116c7261d55527a11e16b1b474f0.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Ohio passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2016 through House Bill 523. The law allows qualifying patients to possess a&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">90-day supply of medical marijuana</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. The amount is to be determined. Cultivation of medical marijuana is not allowed.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-ohio" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
					<div class="news-item newspage-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
									<i class="icon icon-popular"></i>
								<div class="title clearfix">
										<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-north-dakota">
						Understanding Medical Cannabis Regulations in North Dakota
					</a>
				</div>

									<div class="thumb">
						<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(files/9b86d3f19e51bcf765da120cbbc7b62b5ff1c615.jpg);"></div>
					</div>
				
				<div class="source">
									</div>

				<div class="text">
					<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(112, 87, 75);">Nort</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">h Dakota passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2016 through Ballot Measure 5 that received&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">63% of the vote</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. The law allows qualifying patients to possess 3 ounces of medical marijuana. Patients are allowed to cultivate&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">8 cannabis plants&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">if they live more than 40 miles away from a compassionate ca</span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(112, 87, 75);">re center.</span><br></p>
				</div>

				<a href="medical-cannabis/understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-north-dakota" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
			</div>
